  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Alternative housing and fostering of social cohesion in Exarchia, Athens</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved housing situation for refugees and extremely vulnerable Greeks through the provision of 6 rooms (average of 4 people each with a maximum tenancy of 3 months) within a refurbished house in Athens, Exarchia (total 72 people over the project period)
Improved local integration and cohesion within the local community through activities and events reaching a total of 300 people
Psycho-social support for 70 people.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Secured and safe housing for families and vulnerable adults will support social networking, social inclusion and community cohesion. 
The inclusion of impoverished Greeks within the project will support current efforts for integration and mitigate tensions between migrants and Greeks.</narrative>
  </description>
